A teenage boy has appeared in court after being charged with the murder of a 16-year-old who was killed in west London.Police were called to Bourne Avenue, Hayes, on the afternoon of 24 May, following reports of a stabbing.Emergency services tried to save Kamari Johnson, but he died at the scene.The 17-year-old boy, who cannot be named for legal reasons, was arrested and has since been charged with murder and possession of a bladed article in a public place. The Metropolitan Police said the boy appeared in custody at Uxbridge Magistratesâ€™ Court on Monday and has been remanded to to next appear at the Old Bailey on Wednesday.
